          <p><em>From <a href="https://code.google.com/u/115051333155336583554/">markgabb...@gmail.com</a> on March 23, 2012 08:09:04</em></p>

<p>Ciao, I can apply your patch but the project doesn't build. The Fragment class that you use class on Android 3.0 or Android Support Library.</p>

<p>I changed one line of MapFragment.java to use the Fragments from the Android support lib (line 11):</p>

<ul>
<li>import android.app.Fragment;</li>
<li>import android.support.v4.app.Fragment;</li>
</ul>

<p>And then I added to the mapsforge-map pom.xml file the Android support-v4 lib dependency (line 76):</p>

<pre><code>            &lt;dependency&gt;
                    &lt;groupId&gt;com.google.android&lt;/groupId&gt;
                    &lt;artifactId&gt;support-v4&lt;/artifactId&gt;
                    &lt;version&gt; r6 &lt;/version&gt;
                    &lt;scope&gt;provided&lt;/scope&gt;
            &lt;/dependency&gt;
</code></pre>
      </div>
